## chart ambition-loop Plan-Space Ambition and Refinement
```mermaid
flowchart TD
  baseline["Reality baseline"]
  contract["First goal contract"]
  ambition1["Ambition round 1: make pressure useful, not decorative"]
  ambition2["Ambition round 2: remove invented backend nouns"]
  ambition3["Ambition round 3: make pause quality measurable"]
  depth["Domain depth: operator attention, batch triage, action cue trust"]
  tasks["Beads or workgraph with dependencies"]
  refine["Refinement rounds until no meaningful plan gaps remain"]
  frontier["Ready implementation frontier"]

  baseline --> contract --> ambition1 --> ambition2 --> ambition3 --> depth --> tasks --> refine --> frontier

  classDef current fill:#e0f2fe,stroke:#0284c7,color:#0c4a6e,stroke-width:2px
  classDef ambition fill:#ede9fe,stroke:#7c3aed,color:#3b0764,stroke-width:2px
  classDef ready fill:#dcfce7,stroke:#16a34a,color:#14532d,stroke-width:2px
  class baseline,contract current
  class ambition1,ambition2,ambition3,depth,refine ambition
  class tasks,frontier ready
```

## chart hardening-loop Recurring Smart Hardening Loop
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> Describe
  Describe --> Reproduce: define web and cue pass cases
  Reproduce --> Implement: prove current failure first
  Implement --> Tests: smallest reuse-first change
  Tests --> RiskCheck: Rust and JS suites pass
  RiskCheck --> RealityCheck: CRAP or mutation if scope is risky
  RealityCheck --> NextWave: gaps remain
  RealityCheck --> ProofGate: evidence passes
  NextWave --> Describe
  ProofGate --> [*]
```

## chart proof-gate Final Proof Gate
```mermaid
flowchart TD
  cue["Action cues visible end-to-end from clawgs.emit.v2 to SessionSummary"]
  slice["Current web slice: repo structures, agent glyphs, hover freeze, 200 wpm adjustable speed reader, action controls"]
  parity["TUI thought rail and web pressure view agree on needs-input, batch sendability, launch, Mermaid, plan files, and commit controls"]
  web["Web Trogdor HUD renders shared Rust model with keyboard and pointer hit zones"]
  smoke["Live web terminal smoke proves input marker round trip"]
  tests["cargo and node tests for touched Rust and JS paths pass"]
  docs["README or docs explain web-only mode without new backend terminology"]
  commit["Commit if authorized"]
  reality["Post-commit reality-check-for-project agrees"]
  done["LOFTY GOAL MET"]

  cue --> slice --> parity --> web --> smoke --> tests --> docs --> commit --> reality --> done

  classDef required fill:#fee2e2,stroke:#dc2626,color:#7f1d1d,stroke-width:2px
  classDef done fill:#dcfce7,stroke:#16a34a,color:#14532d,stroke-width:3px
  class cue,slice,smoke,tests done
  class parity,web,docs,commit,reality required
  class done done
```

## chart build-vs-clone Build-vs-Clone Reuse Assessment
```mermaid
flowchart TD
  rule["Rule: do not reinvent hardened logic or rename backend concepts"] --> adopt["ADOPT existing contracts"]
  rule --> extract["EXTRACT/BORROW hardened TUI backend logic"]
  rule --> build["BUILD only missing web/game surface"]
  rule --> avoid["DO NOT BUILD"]

  adopt --> session["SessionSummary, SessionState, ThoughtState, RestState, StateEvidence"]
  adopt --> selection["/v1/selection published follow"]
  adopt --> clawgs["clawgs.emit.v2 action_cues"]

  extract --> rail["TUI thought rail: needs-input, batch send, launch, commit, Mermaid, plans"]
  extract --> shared["DONE slice: shared Rust operator pressure model consumed by web"]

  build --> web["DONE slice: web rendering, hit zones, Trogdor presentation, and atlas toggle in rendered_surface.js/app.js"]
  build --> api["DONE slice: narrow swimmers API fields for existing clawgs cues"]

  avoid --> schema["No primary Trogdor event schema"]
  avoid --> rename["No villager_intent or burninate_command backend nouns"]
  avoid --> parser["No raw transcript parser in swimmers"]

  session --> pressure["Pressure is a derived view"]
  clawgs --> pressure
  rail --> pressure
  pressure --> web
  pressure --> labels["Trogdor labels stay presentation-only"]

  classDef avoid fill:#fee2e2,stroke:#dc2626,color:#7f1d1d,stroke-width:2px
  classDef build fill:#fef3c7,stroke:#d97706,color:#78350f,stroke-width:2px
  classDef reuse fill:#dcfce7,stroke:#16a34a,color:#14532d,stroke-width:2px
  classDef neutral fill:#f8fafc,stroke:#64748b,color:#0f172a
  class rule,pressure,labels neutral
  class adopt,extract,session,selection,clawgs,rail,shared reuse
  class build,web,api build
  class avoid,schema,rename,parser avoid
```

## chart wiki-guidance Wiki Direction
```mermaid
flowchart TD
  trogdor["Trogdor essence"] --> race["Attention race: notice blocked agents quickly"]
  trogdor --> pause["Pause quality: fast is bad if it creates rushed human reasoning"]
  observe["Agent observability"] --> metrics["Measure response latency, situation understanding time, and bad intervention rate"]
  gates["Quality gates"] --> gatehabit["Avoid gate habituation"]
  gates --> evidence["Require evidence before autonomy expands"]
  loop["Admin-executor loop"] --> ledger["Actor, intent, gate, executor, command, artifact, follow-up ledger"]
  local["Local-first ownership"] --> web["Browser frontend can be hosted, but backend truth stays local"]

  race --> goal["Smart goal: pressure-aware web operator loop"]
  pause --> goal
  metrics --> goal
  evidence --> goal
  ledger --> goal
  web --> goal

  classDef source fill:#f8fafc,stroke:#64748b,color:#0f172a
  classDef useful fill:#dcfce7,stroke:#16a34a,color:#14532d,stroke-width:2px
  classDef caution fill:#fef3c7,stroke:#d97706,color:#78350f,stroke-width:2px
  class trogdor,observe,gates,loop,local source
  class race,metrics,evidence,ledger,web,goal useful
  class pause,gatehabit caution
```

## chart ux-refinement User Experience Refinement Loop
```mermaid
flowchart TD
  workflow["Target-user workflow: operator scans pressure, chooses session, acts or pauses"]
  parity["TUI parity pass: web preserves sendable, sleeping, batch, commit, plan semantics"]
  interaction["Interaction pass: keyboard focus, pointer zones, terminal handoff, follow selection"]
  visual["Visual pass: dense terminal surface, readable pressure, no card-heavy dashboard drift"]
  responsive["Responsive proof: desktop and narrow viewport stay usable"]
  hover["Implemented slice: hover an agent freezes it and opens 200 wpm adjustable speed reader"]
  controls["Implemented slice: reader exposes send, batch, launch, Mermaid, and commit actions"]
  planfiles["Implemented slice: web Mermaid sheet reads plan sibling files through existing API"]
  e2e["E2E or screenshot proof for full web HUD plus live terminal attach"]
  recheck["Reality check UX claims"]

  workflow --> parity --> interaction --> hover --> controls --> planfiles --> visual --> responsive --> e2e --> recheck

  classDef current fill:#e0f2fe,stroke:#0284c7,color:#0c4a6e,stroke-width:2px
  classDef proof fill:#dcfce7,stroke:#16a34a,color:#14532d,stroke-width:2px
  classDef work fill:#f8fafc,stroke:#64748b,color:#0f172a
  class workflow,parity current
  class interaction,visual,responsive work
  class hover,controls,planfiles,e2e,recheck proof
```
